# Vault System

## Definition
The **Vault System** is my method for treating creative output as preserved value. I archive works as assets with structure, versions, and editions.

## What the Vault stores
- Albums / EPs / singles (masters + lyric files)
- Books / scripts / lore pages
- Visual identity assets (covers, symbols, posters)
- Metadata (release dates, versions, credits)
- Edition logic (standard, deluxe, vault edition)

## Vault taxonomy (simple)
- **Vault Deposit:** any finished work placed into the archive
- **Vault Edition:** an approved version (standard/deluxe/etc.)
- **Vault Seal:** “canon-approved” status
- **Vault Index:** the catalog map (Discography + bibliography)

## Release logic
I treat releases like:
1) Create → 2) Verify → 3) Archive → 4) Publish  
Not publish first and figure it out later.

## Canon discipline
If a title changes, the Vault records:
- old title
- new title
- date
- reason

